# Content Collections – Frontmatter Schemas

## Blog Post (`src/content/blog/*.md`)

```yaml
---
title: "Descriptive title"
date: 2024-06-01          # ISO date — coerced to Date by Zod
description: "One-sentence summary shown in cards and meta tags"
tags: ["AWS", "Terraform"]
---
```

- `date` must be a valid ISO date string
- `tags` is currently validated as an array of strings
- `description` should stay concise because it is reused in meta descriptions and cards

## Project Entry (`src/content/projects/*.md`)

```yaml
---
title: "Project Name"
description: "What problem it solves and how"
technologies: ["Terraform", "AWS", "Karpenter"]
github_link: "https://github.com/..."   # Required, must be a valid URL
demo_link: "https://..."                 # Optional
architecture_notes: "Key design decisions and trade-offs"
---
```

- `github_link` is required and validated as URL
- `demo_link` is optional
- `architecture_notes` is required in the current schema
- `technologies` drives the card labels — keep entries short (e.g. "EKS", not "Amazon EKS")

## Adding a New Collection
1. Define schema in `src/content.config.ts` using `defineCollection` + `z`
2. Export from `collections` object
3. Create folder under `src/content/<name>/`
4. Fetch with `getCollection("<name>")` in pages
